<!-- ===== HERO: the pain ===== -->
<div class="wrap">
  <section class="hero">
    <span class="kicker">A lifelong record for your child</span>
    <h1>Every outcome, captured once.<br><span>Reused everywhere.</span></h1>
    <div class="rule"></div>
    <p class="define">OutcomeStar is one place to record your child's academics, athletics, and achievements &mdash; from age 0 to 18 &mdash; so college applications, resumes, and recruiting profiles fill themselves later, instead of being reconstructed from shoeboxes on a deadline.</p>
    <div class="who-band"><b>Who it's for:</b> Parents of kids ages 0&ndash;18. Start at 3 or start at 16 &mdash; the earlier the record begins, the more senior fall becomes an export instead of a scramble. Athletes get recruiting-ready data. Every student gets an application that fills itself.</div>
    <p class="trust">Built by one dad to get one kid into the right school &mdash; and opened to your family. Not venture-backed. Your record is yours, exportable any time, never deleted.</p>
    <a class="btn" href="/signup">Start your child's record &rarr;</a>
    <span class="sub">Free for ages 0&ndash;10 &middot; Free for needs-based applicants &middot; Cancel anytime</span>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== THE PAIN (moved below the what/who gate) ===== -->
  <section class="sect-head" style="padding-top:8px">
    <span class="kicker">Senior fall is coming</span>
    <h2>Will you be ready?</h2>
  </section>
  <section class="narrow" style="text-align:center;padding-top:14px">
    <p style="max-width:660px;margin:0 auto;font-size:16.5px;color:#4A5563">Every family hits the same wall: applications open in August and suddenly you're excavating twelve years of report cards, race times, certificates, and half-remembered dates from shoeboxes, screenshots, and three dead school portals &mdash; on a deadline.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== PAIN: name the three problems ===== -->
  <section class="sect-head">
    <span class="kicker">The problem</span>
    <h2>Three things go wrong in every admissions season</h2>
  </section>
  <section class="grid">
    <div class="card pain"><h3>The shoebox problem</h3><p>The evidence of your child's whole journey lives in camera rolls, email attachments, gym bags, and portals that lock you out the day they graduate. When applications ask for specifics, nobody can find them.</p></div>
    <div class="card pain"><h3>The timeline anxiety</h3><p>Should a sophomore be testing yet? How many activities is enough? Is this course load rigorous? Without benchmarks, every month carries a quiet fear that you're already behind.</p></div>
    <div class="card pain"><h3>The teenager problem</h3><p>Every tracking app assumes your student will faithfully log in and update it. They won't. The tool gets abandoned by October and the record stops exactly when it matters most.</p></div>
  </section>
  <div class="cta-row">
    <a class="btn" href="/signup">Solve all three &mdash; create your account</a>
    <span class="sub">Free for ages 0&ndash;10 &middot; cancel anytime &middot; your record is never deleted</span>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ===== FEATURE 1 ===== -->
<section class="feature alt">
  <div class="narrow">
    <span class="kicker">What you get &middot; 1 of 6</span>
    <h2>Five pillars, one record</h2>
    <p class="lead">Personal, Academics, Extracurricular, Career, and Higher Education &mdash; every course, test, race, recital, rank, and role captured once and reused everywhere.</p>
    <p class="more">Enter it the day it happens, in minutes. Twelve years later that single entry appears in the application, the resume, the report, and the website &mdash; without ever being typed again.</p>
    <a class="btn" href="/signup">Start your child's record</a>
    <span class="sub">Five minutes to set up &middot; free for ages 0&ndash;10</span>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===== FEATURE 2 ===== -->
<section class="feature">
  <div class="narrow">
    <span class="kicker">What you get &middot; 2 of 6</span>
    <h2>Applications that fill themselves</h2>
    <p class="lead">Generate filled college application forms, tailored resumes, and comprehensive reports directly from your child's verified record.</p>
    <p class="more">Senior fall stops being data entry. Activities lists, honors sections, course histories, and athletic results flow from the record you've kept &mdash; accurate, complete, and ready to review instead of reconstruct.</p>
    <a class="btn" href="/signup">Make senior fall an export</a>
    <span class="sub">The earlier the record starts, the easier that season gets</span>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===== FEATURE 3 ===== -->
<section class="feature alt">
  <div class="narrow">
    <span class="kicker">What you get &middot; 3 of 6</span>
    <h2>A website that grows up</h2>
    <p class="lead">A family memory book at 5, a developmental portfolio at 10, a professional launchpad at 16 &mdash; privacy guardrails enforced at every age, in English and your home language.</p>
    <p class="more">One address, thirty themes, and content that matures with your child. Grandparents visit it today; coaches and admissions officers visit it later. You choose exactly what the world sees.</p>
    <a class="btn" href="/signup">Give your child their site</a>
    <span class="sub">Dual-language sites included on every plan</span>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===== FEATURE 4 ===== -->
<section class="feature">
  <div class="narrow">
    <span class="kicker">What you get &middot; 4 of 6</span>
    <h2>Athletics, tracked properly</h2>
    <p class="lead">Personal records, time standards, and progress analytics &mdash; recruitment-ready data instead of scattered screenshots.</p>
    <p class="more">Every race, meet, and match becomes a data point: PRs by event, standards achieved, trend lines a recruiter can read in ten seconds. When the coach asks for times, you send a link, not a shoebox.</p>
    <a class="btn" href="/signup">Track the first season free</a>
    <span class="sub">Built for swimmers first &mdash; works for every sport</span>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===== FEATURE 5 ===== -->
<section class="feature alt">
  <div class="narrow">
    <span class="kicker">What you get &middot; 5 of 6</span>
    <h2>Built by a parent</h2>
    <p class="lead">Created for one family's road to college and opened to yours. Your data stays yours &mdash; generate a report of everything stored, any time.</p>
    <p class="more">This isn't a venture-backed engagement machine. It's the system one father built to get one kid to the right school &mdash; and every family that joins gets the same machinery, the same care, and the same exit door: your complete record, free, whenever you ask.</p>
    <a class="btn" href="/signup">Join the founding families</a>
    <span class="sub">Founding pricing locked for the life of the account</span>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===== FEATURE 6 ===== -->
<section class="feature">
  <div class="narrow">
    <span class="kicker">What you get &middot; 6 of 6</span>
    <h2>Private by default</h2>
    <p class="lead">Child sites use first-name-only public pages, nondescript links, and no-index protection. Law first, parent second, child by age.</p>
    <p class="more">Every record starts private. Nothing appears publicly without your explicit per-item choice, and platform rules for minors apply no matter what &mdash; no last names, no addresses, no search engines. COPPA-verified consent is built into signup itself.</p>
    <a class="btn" href="/signup">Create a private record today</a>
    <span class="sub">Verified parental consent &middot; per-family database isolation</span>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===== TIMELINE ===== -->
<div class="wrap">
  <section class="sect-head">
    <span class="kicker">How it plays out</span>
    <h2>The road is long. The work each year is small.</h2>
  </section>
  <section class="timeline">
    <div class="tl-row"><div class="tl-when">Ages 0&ndash;10</div><div class="tl-what">Free. Capture firsts, milestones, sports, and keepsakes &mdash; ten minutes a month builds a record no memory can match.</div></div>
    <div class="tl-row"><div class="tl-when">Middle school</div><div class="tl-what">Courses, activities, and early achievements start shaping the story &mdash; benchmarks show where depth is building.</div></div>
    <div class="tl-row"><div class="tl-when">Grades 9&ndash;11</div><div class="tl-what">Transcripts, test scores, leadership ranks, and athletic times accumulate verified &mdash; the profile colleges actually evaluate.</div></div>
    <div class="tl-row"><div class="tl-when">Senior fall</div><div class="tl-what">Applications, resumes, and recommendation packets generate from twelve years of record &mdash; an export, not a scramble.</div></div>
  </section>
  <div class="cta-row" style="padding-top:20px">
    <a class="btn" href="/signup">Start where you are today</a>
    <span class="sub">Whether your child is 3 or 16 &mdash; the best day to start the record is today</span>
  </div>
